# Create GraphQL Resolver

Pattern for adding a resolver:

1. One file per domain context: `auth_resolver.go`, `user_resolver.go`, `settings_resolver.go`
2. Resolver struct holds use case interfaces
3. Auth-protected resolvers must call `middleware.UserIDFromContext(ctx)`
4. Return `*model.XxxPayload` from mutations
5. Never leak domain internals (password hashes, tokens in logs, etc.)

```go
package resolver

import (
    "context"

    "github.com/masterfabric/masterfabric_go_basic/internal/application/<context>/dto"
    "github.com/masterfabric/masterfabric_go_basic/internal/infrastructure/graphql/model"
    "github.com/masterfabric/masterfabric_go_basic/internal/shared/middleware"
)

func (r *mutationResolver) XxxMutation(ctx context.Context, input model.XxxInput) (*model.XxxPayload, error) {
    req := &dto.XxxRequest{
        // map input → request DTO
    }
    resp, err := r.xxxUseCase.Execute(ctx, req)
    if err != nil {
        return nil, err
    }
    return &model.XxxPayload{
        // map response DTO → GraphQL model
    }, nil
}
```
